<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CATERPILLAR 3176B AND 3406E ELECTRONIC ENGINES - DIAGNOSTICS AND TROUBLESHOOTING - THROTTLE
        POSITION SENSOR (TPS)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>THROTTLE POSITION SENSOR (TPS)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) And Circuits</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (400) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0805712" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 7 - Testing Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) And Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING THROTTLE POSITION SENSOR (TPS) AND CIRCUITS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect TPS from cab harness at connector (404). At TPS side of (404) measure
                                    resistance to gnd at A, B and C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404) A, B and C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the throttle position sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (400) from ECM. At (404) measure resistance between terminals
                                    A, B and C. There should be no continuity between the three terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404) between A, B and C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short circuit between any circuit where resistance is less than 100K ohms
                                    between the terminals, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to gnd. At connector (404)
                                    measure resistance to gnd at terminal B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(137) A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99-G path to gnd, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to 37. At connector (404)
                                    measure resistance between terminals B and C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(404) B to C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99 between connectors (404) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (400), use test lead to jumper terminal 29 to 35. At connector (404)
                                    measure resistance between terminals B and A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(404) B to A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 99E between connectors (404) and (400),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Connect (400) to ECM. Turn ignition ON. At connector (404) measure voltage between
                                    terminals A and B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(421) 47/48 (+) to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>8&#177; 0.5 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Have Caterpillar dealer diagnose the ECM.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the throttle position sensor, reconnect connectors. Test system operation
                                    and note if defect is still present. TPS works OK?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>End test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Have Caterpillar dealer diagnose the ECM.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
